    <!-- Microhydro Power Plant Info -->
    <div class="content">
        <div class="microhydro-info">
            <h2>What is a Microhydro Power Plant?</h2>
            <p>A microhydro power plant is a small-scale, renewable energy system that generates electricity from the flow of water. These systems are typically used in rural or remote areas where access to traditional power grids is limited or unavailable. Microhydro power plants are ideal for locations with a reliable and steady water source, such as rivers or streams.</p>
            <p>These plants work by channeling the flowing water through a turbine, which converts the kinetic energy of the water into mechanical energy. This mechanical energy is then converted into electrical energy through a generator.</p>
            <h3>Benefits of Microhydro Power Plants for Villages</h3>
            <p>Microhydro power plants can significantly reduce electricity costs for an entire village. Once set up, they can provide a continuous and reliable source of power, eliminating the need for expensive electricity imports or diesel generators. These plants are also environmentally friendly, as they produce clean, renewable energy with minimal environmental impact.</p>
            <p>By harnessing the power of flowing water, villages can achieve energy independence, reduce reliance on fossil fuels, and lower the overall cost of electricity for the community. Moreover, microhydro systems require less maintenance compared to other renewable sources like solar or wind, making them a cost-effective and sustainable solution for long-term energy needs.</p>
        </div>
